<br>{{Blurimage|file=Phenomeon123Picture.png|caption=An image of Phenomenon 123 occurring. The excessive heat severely damaged the camera taking the photo.}}Phenomenon 123, commonly referred to as "Regenerative Combustion", is an occurrence in which a Wanderer inexplicably explodes in a level and awakes without recollection of the event. The research for why is still ongoing and so far has only returned with Inconclusive results along with 12 fatalities.Regenerative Combustion can occur in any level of the Backrooms where oxygen and ground is present. The reason for the ground parameter is not known yet. Explosion severity are completely dependent on the affected individual. (i.e. Height, Weight, Age) Sex does not change the severity. Reports have stated that an individual can explode more than once and that the blast radius will increase each time.

Reports have shown that before the explosion individuals nearby can hear an audible high-pitched "ringing" sound akin to a train whistle or tinnitus. The time in which the sound continues is variable, thought it does immediately cease after the  affected individual goes through Regenerative Combustion.

Victims have reported that they do not recall Regenerative Combustion taking place. Though, they do recall an increase in core temperature after the event concluded. Victims that had exploded more than once reported having "fever like symptoms". One instance of Phenomenon 123 resulted in the victim immediately dying to hyperthermia. A laser thermometer recorded a surface skin temperature of over 150° Fahrenheit (~66° Celsius). Heat warping was recorded coming from the body. Although the skin was not severely burnt. While affected individuals do not remember the event, they will '''"remanifest with a profound sense of terror"'''. As one survivor claimed.

Individuals who explode will materialize without external injury. As stated previously, the affected individual will not recall exploding. Another abnormal characteristic of Regenerative Combustion is the victim's inability to perceive the damage dealt by the blast. Multiple fatalities have been reported because of this. In that rare circumstance, the victim unknowingly stepps into a blaze caused by their explosion and may be burnt to death.

Individuals in the blast radius will suffer irreversible damage. Even after the victim has materialized.

Reports in levels with low carbon dioxide levels have a significantly lower report frequency than other levels. Levels with high carbon dioxide levels have the opposite effect.

